  "hash": "sha256:3f8a1c2e9d047b56f1a3c8e2d094f7b3a1e6c5d2f0b9a4e7c3d1f8b2a5e9c06d",
  "signature": "ed25519:7a3b1d9f2c4e8a0b5d6f1e3c7a9b2d4f6e8a0c2b4d6f8a0c2e4b6d8f0a2c4e6b",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "SQA procedures documented and traceable to GAMP 5 Category 4 requirements; version-controlled solver with audit trail.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 was deployed under a validated installation qualification (IQ) and operational qualification (OQ) protocol consistent with GAMP 5 Category 4. All simulation scripts were version-controlled in a Git repository with commit hashes recorded in the simulation log. Change control procedures were followed for all post-baseline modifications. SQA documentation reviewed and approved by the quality assurance team prior to study initiation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver verified against at least one benchmark problem with known analytical or highly accurate reference solution relevant to rotating machinery flows.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent was verified against the Taylor-Couette flow benchmark, confirming correct implementation of the rotating reference frame formulation. Velocity profiles matched the analytical solution to within 0.3% across the gap. Additionally, the MRF (multiple reference frame) implementation was cross-checked against a published DNS dataset for a simplified impeller geometry, yielding torque predictions within 2.1% of the reference."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI < 5% on the quantity of interest (NIH) for the production mesh; observed order of convergence within 10% of nominal scheme order.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation performed on three systematically refined meshes. GCI on the fine mesh was 2.1% for NIH, comfortably below the 5% threshold. Observed order of convergence p = 1.94 is consistent with the second-order upwind scheme. Spatial discretization error is not a dominant uncertainty source at the production mesh resolution of 8.4M cells."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions documented with sufficient detail to reproduce boundary conditions in CFD; fluid properties and pump operating parameters recorded.",
      "rationale": "In vitro hemolysis experiments were conducted in a closed-loop flow circuit with phosphate-buffered saline and bovine blood at 37°C. Flow rates were measured with a calibrated ultrasonic transit-time flowmeter (±1.5% accuracy). Rotational speed was monitored via optical tachometer. Temperature was controlled to ±0.5°C. All boundary conditions applied in CFD were directly traceable to the experimental test report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (mean relative error or equivalent) defined a priori; CFD predictions within pre-specified acceptance band across all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "Mean relative error in NIH across five operating points was 11.3%, within the pre-specified 15% acceptance band established in the validation plan prior to data analysis. Individual point errors ranged from 4.2% to 14.8%. The RH criterion (RH < 1.0) was satisfied at all five operating points. The comparison metric and acceptance threshold were documented in the validation plan before unblinding of experimental results."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI used in validation (NIH) is directly linked to the COU decision quantity (RH); mapping between validation QoI and COU QoI is documented.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) used in validation experiments is the direct precursor to the relative hemolysis index (RH) used in the COU acceptance criterion. The mapping RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate is explicitly documented in the analysis plan. Both quantities are computed from the same CFD scalar transport model for red blood cell damage, ensuring direct relevance of the validation QoI to the COU decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments performed on the same device geometry or a geometrically similar predicate; operating conditions span the COU envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments were conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which shares the same impeller topology as the subject device but differs in volute exit angle by approximately 12 degrees. While the five validation operating points bracket the nominal COU conditions, the upper bound of the COU speed envelope (4800 RPM) was not included in the validation dataset; the highest validated speed was 4500 RPM. The assessment team judged this gap acceptable given the monotonic NIH-speed relationship observed across the validated range, and the COU decision was accepted. The achieved level of 1 reflects the partial coverage of the COU operating envelope and the geometric dissimilarity at the volute, which were noted but not treated as disqualifying."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated; residuals and monitored QoI reach stable values within accepted tolerances.",
      "rationale": "All simulations were run to scaled residual convergence of 1e-5 for continuity and momentum equations. NIH monitor point variation over the final 500 iterations was less than 0.1%. No divergence or non-physical oscillation was observed in any of the five operating-point simulations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by an independent analyst; boundary condition assignments and material property inputs verified against the test report.",
      "rationale": "An independent senior CFD analyst reviewed the simulation setup, including boundary condition assignments, material property inputs, and turbulence model parameters, against the test report and analysis plan. No discrepancies were identified. The review was documented in a formal review record signed by both the primary analyst and the reviewer."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor; scoped out per the credibility assessment plan.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty (turbulence model, hemolysis power-law exponent selection) was not formally quantified at MRL 2. A qualitative sensitivity study comparing two turbulence models was performed as part of the validation activity and showed NIH divergence of 8.7%, which was judged acceptable. Formal model form assessment is deferred to MRL 3 activities if device risk classification is elevated."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; input uncertainty propagation deferred.",
      "rationale": "Formal uncertainty propagation of model input parameters (blood viscosity, RBC mechanical properties, power-law damage coefficients) was not performed at MRL 2. Nominal values sourced from peer-reviewed literature (Giersiepen et al., 1990; Zhang et al., 2011) were used throughout. Sensitivity to ±10% variation in the damage exponent was evaluated informally and showed less than 6% change in NIH, supporting the adequacy of nominal inputs for the current COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; sample variability characterization deferred.",
      "rationale": "Biological variability in bovine blood samples used for in vitro experiments was not formally characterized. Three independent blood draws were used across the five operating points, and batch-to-batch NIH variability was estimated at approximately 7% based on repeat measurements at the nominal operating point. This variability was noted in the experimental report but was not propagated into the credibility assessment at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; equivalency mapping deferred.",
      "rationale": "Formal equivalency assessment between experimental input parameters and CFD boundary conditions was not performed at MRL 2. Boundary conditions were set to match nominal experimental values directly. Discrepancies between measured and applied inlet velocity profiles were estimated at less than 3% based on flowmeter calibration uncertainty, and were judged to have negligible impact on NIH predictions at the current level of assessment."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 ASME V&V 40 factors and determined that the CFD model meets the requirements for Model Risk Level 2 credibility. Seven factors were formally assessed; six were scoped out as not required at MRL 2. All assessed factors were judged to meet or exceed required levels, with the validation comparison demonstrating mean relative error of 11.3% within the pre-specified 15% acceptance band. The relative hemolysis index satisfied RH < 1.0 across all five operating points. The overall assurance level is declared Medium, reflecting the structured validation activities, documented uncertainty characterization, and independent review of simulation setup. The partial coverage of the COU speed envelope in validation experiments was noted and judged acceptable given the monotonic NIH-speed relationship. The decision to accept the model for the stated COU is supported by the totality of evidence presented in this package.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
